Class SubscriptionService

java.lang.Object
  com.paymill.services.SubscriptionService

public class SubscriptionService
extends Object

The SubscriptionService is used to list, create, edit, delete and update PAYMILL Subscriptions.

createWithOfferAndPayment

public Subscription createWithOfferAndPayment(Offer offer,
                                              Payment payment)
This function creates a Subscription between a Client and an Offer. A Client can have several Subscriptions to different Offers, but only one Subscription to the same Offer. The Clients is charged for each billing interval entered.
NOTE
This call will use the Client from the Payment object.

Parameters:
offer - An Offer to subscribe to.
payment - A Payment used for charging.
Returns:
Subscription, which allows you to charge recurring payments.

update

public void update(Subscription subscription)
This function updates the Subscription of a Client. You can change e.g. the cancelAtPeriodEnd attribute to terminate a Subscription at a special point of time. Or you can change the Payment. All other edited properties will be set back to its source defined in PAYMILL.

Parameters:
subscription - A Subscription with cancelAtPeriodEnd or Payment.

delete

public void delete(Subscription subscription)
This function removes an existing subscription. If you set the attribute cancelAtPeriodEnd parameter to the value true, the subscription will remain active until the end of the period. The subscription will not be renewed again. If the value is set to false it is directly terminated, but pending Transactions will still be charged.

Parameters:
subscription - A Subscription with Id to be deleted.

delete

public void delete(String subscriptionId)
This function removes an existing subscription. If you set the attribute cancelAtPeriodEnd parameter to the value true, the subscription will remain active until the end of the period. The subscription will not be renewed again. If the value is set to false it is directly terminated, but pending Transactions will still be charged.

Parameters:
subscriptionId - Id of the Subscription, which have to be deleted.
